> One of the most popular dishes in Korean cuisine, bibimbap is a rice bowl dish. The word bibim means to mix while bap is rice. It's a dish that lends itself well to customisations, and this delicious veggie version features pickled carrot and crispy fried tofu.

Peel and grate the @ginger{1%unit}. Use a spoon to easily scrape away the peel.

Place a #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Fry the ginger for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @cold salted water{300%ml}. Bring to the boil,
lower the heat to medium and cover with the #lid{}.

Cook for ~{12%minutes}, then remove the pot from the heat. Keep covered for
another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook
in its own steam).

Meanwhile, drain the @Tofu{280%g} and chop into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with
#kitchen paper{}.

Toss the tofu chunks with half the @Soy Sauce{1%sachet}.

Place a #pan{} over high heat with a good glug of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the tofu until slightly crispy, ~{6-8%minutes}. Shift frequently
to ensure it doesn't burn.

Once cooked, remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, trim and peel the @Carrot{1%unit}.

Make long ribbons by running the #peeler{} down the length of the carrot,
stopping at the core.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @Apple Cider Vinegar{1%sachet},
@Salt{1/2%tsp}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @warm water{1%tbsp}.

Once mixed, add the carrot ribbons.

Set aside, continuing to mix at regular intervals.

Peel and grate the @Garlic{1%unit}.

Strip the leafy part of the @Kale{80%g} from the stem and tear into small
pieces. Discard the stem (it's too tough to eat).

Roughly chop the @Mushrooms{150%g}.

In a small bowl, mix the @Sesame Oil{20%ml}, @Gochujang Paste{1%sachet}
(use less if you don't like spice) and remaining soy sauce.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Fry the kale, mushrooms and garlic until softened, stirring occasionally,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Season to taste with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

Fluff up the ginger rice and divide between #bowls{}.

Layer the pickled carrot, fried veg and tofu on top.

Finish with a drizzle of the spicy sesame sauce.